<dl id="n38220c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38220c">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38220c"> 220(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sherbet</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The first mention of coffee proper <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> is in Night cdxxvi. vol. v. 169 <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> As the work advances notices become thicker, <i>e.g.</i> in Night dcclxvi.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> and in Abu Kir and Abu Sir (Nights cmxxx. and cmxxxvi.) where coffee is drunk with <mark>sherbet</mark> after the present fashion. <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE1"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 90n4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
